Sec. 152.001. TRAINING PROGRAM FOR HORSE OWNERS. (a) The
Texas Agricultural Extension Service shall develop an ongoing
training program for horse owners to promote the prevention of horse
theft. The program must include information on visible, permanent
identification of horses and other security measures to prevent horse
theft.
(b) A county office of the Texas Agricultural Extension Service
periodically shall notify horse owners of the training program
through public service announcements or other means.
Added by Acts 1997, 75th Leg., ch. 780, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1997.
Renumbered from Agriculture Code Sec. 151.001 by Acts 1999, 76th
Leg., ch. 62, Sec. 19.01(1), eff. Sept. 1, 1999.

